PositiveComments: Matt assisted me and was very knowledgeable and helpful. Because of him, I will come back for the excellent customer service.
Gerald always has a great attitude and is very helpful.
We were recommended to go to this shop and see the man who runs it. He is honest and good.  We were completely satisfied and will be going back.
The manager of Longpoint, Mr. Mark, is so kind and helpful. He is also very knowledgeable of his job. You're so fortunate to have him.

David,  the manager at 5820 Kirby Dr  Houston  TX 77005, was very professional and honest. As I am knowledgeable on auto repair, he told me what I already knew,  so right away I trusted him. He gave me a fair price, and Jacorey (Corey) did the work correctly...They fixed my truck twice in the last two months (Brakes and wheel bearing). Corey and David are 2 thumbs up kind of guys.
Paul did a great custom job on my exhaust. Very neat and exactly what i asked for.
I had told them that I wanted to replace my rotors, and your people talked me out of it and saved me $100 by machining them instead!
Staff and service was great.
Good customer service- knows me by first name. Even though I worked across the street and could see that my car was done, I still received a call that it was ready!
Quick analysis and diagnosis of problem with recommended solution in a professional and timely manner.
Lynn  Fritz  and Chris are great to deal with. They make you feel like they care about you and your car.
David helped me out a lot. He yook his time to find the right parts for my vehicle.
The guys at Meineke in Newburgh  NY are AWESOME!

That day was very hot and uncomfortable. When I arrived to the Arlington shop, John was very quick to settle me into the cool waiting room as he attended my needs immediately.  My car was done very soon and I was on my way!  I  was glad to share my experience with my co-workers the next day.
Thanks to all members.

Larry  Glenn and the entire Meineke team are extremely courteous and helpful.  I have been taking my vehicles there for years and feel like I can trust them completely to get an accurate diagnosis and a fair price.  They have always tried to work to give me advice on what repairs need to be done. In today's world, with the complexity of vehicles,  I find that trust is the number one most important trait to look for in a car care center.  I appreciate being able to completely trust this Meineke location.

Everyone was really helpful and friendly. They showed me what all needed to be worked on and explained all of the possibilities of what might happen. I really appreciated them taking me back to my home and picking me up afterwards. It took less than half a day and made my life a lot easier.

I pull into the shop a little after 8:00 AM. I needed a catalytic converter. They had one  but there were 3 cars in front of me. The manager, John Brittingham was able to get a tech working right away. My stay there was pleasant,  and I was able to see how they operate. They are very conscious and considerate of there customer's needs  making sure we understand what needs to be done and trying to find the best parts for the best price. I was so impressed that I took a stack of their cards,  which I will give to family members when  they need work done.
My car was taken in for service as soon as possible.
The guy who runs this shop is knowledgeable and trustworthy. The work was done quickly and at a reasonable price. I appreciate him explaining all of the details of the different services to me.

I am a repeat customer. The two occasions that I have been there  I was welcomed by John. He did a great job with my vehicles. He offered great and reasonable recommendations, and the service was impeccable. John and his team were very thorough with my trucks and the environment they provide at the Webster  TX location is very comfortable and professional.  I had some great conversations with John while I waited! I will definately be coming back to this location for all my vehicles maintenance and repairs. I trust the service they provide,  the work they do, and the amazing service I was provided by their employees. I have recommended meineike to my friends and family and they were pleased with the services they got at meineike as well.  *thumbs up*     -JL
Everything was done well. The quality of service and the professionalism of the staff.

Friendly staff. John explained maintenance work that would be done with my next oil change. My windshield wipers were bad, so they changed them while I was there. It helped with all this rain we have been having.

John Brittingham  really took care of me by  making recommendations  and discussing other repair work needed on another vehicle I own.  These guys are top notch,  and I really like companies that support our Veterans.
The service was done in a timely fashion. The staff that I had contact with were also very helpful.
Vinny was excellent . Great customer service skills. Worked at identifying the root cause of customers issue and created a solution.
I had an early appointment and had to go to work after. The team was ready for me and finished my brakes and oil change quickly. I appreciate on time, fast and expert service. Thank you.
Place was very clean and everyone was very helpful and friendly.
Randy is the best at what he does
Very courteous.

Dave is the manager at this location and he is amazing to work with.  I am a young female and often worry that car centers will take advantage of me.  I never have to worry about that at this location.  Dave is always willing to explain things to me and work with me so that I save money while getting the needed services completed.  I have recommended this location to many people and will continue to do so.
The associate is always kind and honest about how long I will be waiting before he can get to me.
Jay has outstanding customer service!
Sandy and his crew are great.
Explained the reason why the ac wasn't working.
A/C had numerous leaks. Larry worked tediously until my car was perfect. They kept me informed on what was going on while also making me as comfortable as possible.

Mr. Rick would be very proud of the guys that have taken over the shop. They do a  phenomenal job at whal they do. With this specific location being as busy as it always is and for them to still have a positive friendly attitude is amazing. Way to go guys  y'all rock!
I found very friendly and professions employees. Always very satisfied with the work done on my vehicle.

I started coming to this shop when I moved into the neighborhood about 4 years ago. Frank has always been professional and has communicated well with me with everything that needed to be done with my car. He also reminded me about my inspection last year. I feel that I can trust him with my car and I am confident in the work that gets done.
Very friendly , fair and fast.
The manager, James, and staff are always great. They are friendly and professional.
I took my car in for an oil change. The staff was friendly and they put a sticker for my next oil change that was actually legible- a hard feature for a lot of other places!
Ryan has always been knowledgeable and helpful. We have been going to him and this location for years.

Ryan Babiger and his techs always take good care of me  especially when I'm going to take a trip and I ask them to check the ca out. They let me know if something needs attention and of course it gets taken care of.

I went in for a simple oil change and the technician saw that my air filter was crudy. He  brought it out to show me and compared against a new one and suggested that I change it, but it was completely optional. I was very pleased that they took the time to describe/show me the difference of my air filter to help with my decision. Very friendly staff from check in to check out. :)
Dave and Mike are great.  I really trust them with all of our vehicles and have even brought our nieces and nephew's vehicle .
The staff is always very polite and welcoming and explains everything in detail.
This is not my first time at this location! Bruce has always been the most professional. He has repaired several of our cars over the years and has always done a great job!!

I thought I had an expensive brake problem. The tech diagnosed a loose wheel and  tightened all my wheels and said my brakes were fine. I never would have known had you installed new rotors and pads, which would have been costly.  Very honest business.
Always a great experience.  Well run business. Very good prices and service.

I have been bringing my cars to Meineke in Reading,  MA for the past 6-1/2 years and know and trust everyone who works there. The previous and current owners are kind and caring and take good care of me and my car. Them and their staff are knowledgeable and helpful and explain issues clearly. They are always willing to go the extra mile (sometimes literally!) for their customers.
Mike and his team do outstanding work.

I made my appointment with Mike. He is always great to talk to about my car's problems.  Paul, the technician, who serviced my car, is a very knowledgeable person who was able to answer all of my questions while carrying himself in a very professional manner.  By the time it was all finished, all 3 of my car problems were solved. Paul even replaced a pair of worn out tires that would not pass inspection next month.
Chris is professional and accommodating.
All the workers were very helpful! I go back because they are courteous and get the job done right the first time.
Friendly, courteous and clean.
Went above and beyond to take care of every issue I had. Everyone was very nice.
The man who worked the front desk was very friendly and helpful in the questions I had. The service was fast, and I am satisfied.
Tim is excellent!!!

Your Manager is friendly, kind, fast and provides good service. They offered a cold drink, which is super nice. Also, nice waiting area. Met some nice people while being there and sold them a home!  Thanks for a job well done!  You picked the right guy as MANAGER!!!!!
Customer service was amazing. They made me feel like I was a part of the family. Also, the work performed was immaculate.
Will Williams did the oil change and also noticed that the rear brakes would need new pads and rotors in the future. I plan to return to have the work done at a later time.
Roland and Charlie make everything easy. I walked in  and within minutes the team had found the problem and addressed it.
I was greeted with a smile by the girl at check in desk.  The manager explained everything being done.  The mechanic also showed me some areas to watch for possible problems under the car.
We had an appointment . They stuck to the appointment. Got us in and out in a timely manner.
Everyone was great.
The staff explain to me the technical needs of my service in a manner that any layman could understand.
Everyone  was so welcoming and honest. This location will become my go to place going forward. The level of service  provided made me a raving fan.
Always very friendly and quick service!
Bob is a very knowledgeable and courteous person.

I dropped my car off during the night  and promptly received a call in the morning about what service was required (flex pipe). I had the service done and it was finished before noon. I am extremely happy with the workmanship and quality of service.
The only reason why I keep going to Meineke, located in Branford, is because Bob and his staff mechanics, like Jason, keep up the good work.
Mike is a very well trained mechanic in all aspects  of taking your car under his care.
Phil and his crew are an established car care center and are valued as trustworthy people you can count on.
Phil and his crew treat us like one of the family. We can trust them to keep our cars on the road!!
Larry and team, keep up the great work!
Team is terrific.

The owner,  I believe his name is Jaime, is a great all around guy.  He is very friendly, honest, responsive, and helpful.  He never tries to pressure me into anything and always explains everything that is done or should be done to the vehicle.  I rarely complete surveys but felt strongly enough about Jaime and his location to take the time to respond.  In fact, I even created a Yelp account just to review the location because the service and experience was so good.

The service technician (I've forgotten his name  as this was weeks ago) was very helpful talking with the customer service staff with dealing with some confusion on the credit limit on my Meineke card.
Very inforemitive and very honest. I always trust my car issues with this shop. I have been going here for years.
JC in Salem is great !! So friendly and helpful!!  I scheduled an appointment online but it did not go through -
Glen is very knowledgeable and a great person to talk to.
Work was completed very fast and I was on my way much sooner than expected.  Everything that was found was explained to me.
Customer service is done so well. I'm also a regular so they're extra friendly
Joe and his staff are very personable and professional.
Joe and mark are both knowledgeable, friendly, and very professional.

I went in because I had a small exhaust leak on a car I just bought. I believe the man that helped was named Brian. He was extremely helpful and knowledgeable. It was nice knowing my car was in good hands. I ended up getting my car inspection sticker at the same time there.

Quality and quick service for everything from insp. stickers to repairs.  Most of the repairs have been completed within an hour or two after dropoff.  I've only been there 3-4 times  and the staff member I usually see is Bill in the Beverly location - very friendly  knowledgeable  and answers all my questions regarding repairs.
Thanks for fast  friendly service!
Ryan and Austin were awesome and went above expectations to help.
Ryan is a true professional.  His service, flexibility, and attentiveness to my F-150 was top notch.
Needed an alignment and the advisor was able to work me in on a Saturday.
Great knowledgeable staff!
Dwayne is Great ... He always explains everything....After doing my research, they even ordered tires at a good price.
The service was completed in a timely manner. I had no problems at all. The staff was very efficient.
Very professional staff.
I went to one location and they were busy with a two hour wait. Instead of letting me walk out, they callede their other location and got me in. Great Service.
Chris was an outstanding staff member and thoroughly explained the issues he discovered with my truck during the oil change.  The price was fair and service of the brake repair was outstanding.

I had a battery give out on me while driving back one night from Jefferson City, MO to Springfield, MO.  I was able to get a jump and make it home but was leaving for another 3 hour trip the next afternoon and didn't want to be on the road with a faulty old battery.  The next morning I called Goodyear first thing, since they're the shop my dad and my family usually used. They may or may not have been able to fix it and if they could have, it would have taken all day.  I then called Meineke, who I have had good work done by before, and they were able to fit me right in that morning. Not only did they replace my battery, but changed a long overdue oil change for me as well. This was all in the timeframe of about 2 hours since I placed the call into their location.  I'll be calling them first next time and continuing to do so in the future because I was extremely satisfied with all aspects.
Mike has been servicing our family's cars for 11 years now, and I wouldn't think of going anywhere else. He is fair, honest, and a great guy as well. Enjoy working with him.

Mike at the Cedar Rapids  council street location  is absolutely wonderful. He always makes time for us. His crew of skilled mechanics always do a quick and fantastic job. We have had many parts replaced after coming in just for an oil change because they took the time to make sure our car was in the best running condition.
Took a long time but cheap price.
Staff was great. They informed me of the cost if an extra service was needed. Once I decided on it,  it was performed in a timely manner.

I was told what needed to be done. They showed me the damaged part when it was removed to explain what was wrong with it. I was given a heads up about future repairs that might be on the horizon, but I wasn't pressured or deceived into making the repairs right away. Thankful for that.
Always friendly, honest and good guys.
I have been taking our cars here for state inspections for years. They are so nice and know a lot of people by name. Next repair will be done there!
They do quality work at a reasonable price.

Customer service is excellent! They take their time with customers at the counter and over the phone. I was there when there was a rude/disrespectful person on the phone and you guys were very patient, nice and helped solve the issue. I'll come here anytime I need something because of the respect and honesty. Keep it up!!
Good customer service and the time for the oil change was reasonable.
The man at the desk was very professional and friendly. The inside of the building is in need of some serious repair.
I think the thing that impressed me the most is that they tried to repair my truck using the least expensive alternative.

Love this place.  Manager is respectful and knowledgeable. Julian did a great job on my car and excellent job explaining it to me.  Another young man, Matt I think, helped me previously and was excellent as well.  Very kind people.  Thanks!

I wasn't waiting long. One of the guys interacted positively with my child. Was very welcoming. Also, great attitude. He asked me if there was anything else wrong with my car, and I responded yes and gave him vague detail. He was able to pin point exactly what was wrong with my car where I could easily understand. The advice he gave me actually did work. I can tell he takes absolute pride in the accuracy of his performance so that immediately gained my trust. Unlike other car repair companies, I know my car will perform better. Unfortunately, I can't remember his name but there is a picture on the wall of him posing with George Foreman I believe. Hope that helps.
Big Todd is always honest and fair.

This specific location is very great. Professional tone and words are always used. The staff are always super friendly and helpful. I love how fast they process my car. I always get told a longer wait than what it ends up being, which makes me happy. Thank you Meineke and staff.

Was originally told by another shop that I was going to have to replace everything from my catalytic converter back to my muffler. I Brought my car into the Meineke shop in Madison Heights. It took less time than it did to get back to my job when they called me to tell me that I only had to replace my muffler! They also made sure that a tech who specialized in exhaust problems was going to be working when I brought my car in! Someone even stayed late to make sure I could pick up my car the same day I dropped it off! Wonderful team and wonderful service!

I was able to get my brakes changed after work (5pm). Meineke is the only shop open in the area. They fixed my breaks the next morning, and I picked up my car after work. They did their service quickly and on the price I was quoted . I'm very happy with their quality of work .
I had bad experiences with many auto repair shops. Finally, Meineke is a place that I feel confident going home and knowing they did a job well done.

Chad, the Service Manager at the Westchester, Illinois location, has been very helpful in helping me to understand which repairs are immediate and which ones I can hold off on, thus saving me money. He is also always helpful in answering all my questions.
The owner and employees are very nice and explain things well.  They suggest what the car needs and are not pushy.  I love this place for the work done and their customer service.  No complaints.

Tom was professional and assisted with making my appointment and getting my car in quickly.  Isaiah performed the repair and did an awesome, clean job with the welding of the new exhaust piece.  The shop was booked solid for the day shortly after opening.  Everyone was kind, professional and knowledgeable.
Bill is a very good manager and is always looking out for my vehicle maintenance for my 4 car family.
At the location that I visit, manager Grady is always very helpful and honest. Prices are usualy competitive or lower than other places.
Grady is my most trusted car care professional. I recommend him to all my friends.
I went to Meineke to get a second opinion. I was greeted and treated with respect and honesty. The staff as a whole is why I will forever be a Meineke customer.

Roger is an excellent manager.  He explained all I needed to do in order to once again have a safe car. Roger let me know the prices and labor for each part.  The techs that worked on my car had to do a great amount of heavy labor and quality service. I cannot THANK Roger and his team enough for their excellent service.  The Meineke Car Care Company should recognize one of the best centers around. Thanks once again. Sincerely, Thomas J. Magnuson
Owner was there and informed me of in and outs of service to help me understand the process. This was very kind.
The service manager at the South Walnut St  Bloomington, IN shop, EJ,  is top notch.  He is the main reason this is my go-to auto service shop.

Had my oil changed. I also needed my air filter replaced, so I replaced it. I get right in because I make an appointment. EJ and Tommy are always friendly and helpful. This is the only Meineke I go to. I feel like they know my car so that helps to diagnose what or if there is a problem.. The shop is always clean. Thank You.
You let me use a loner to get to work!
Jon took very good care making sure the issue with my car was taken care of. I will be coming back because of him.
I arrived early and they explained how long the service would take. They were very accurate on their estimate.
Bob and Doug always give us their best. It's nice to go to a business who knows you and are familiar with your cars. You can trust them to not sell you on anything you do not need.
Great Team...very efficient and Professional.
I am very happy when coming to this location. When Jessy is not working though because she makes me feel uncomfortable.
Pat is a great manager.

I visited the Meineke location in Turnersville, NJ. The mechanic, William Castelow, was very friendly, professional, and knowledgeable. Typically, when I take my vehicle to get an oil change, I get the complaints about having a German vehicle and how much of a pain they are for repairs or maintenance. Mr. Castelow seemed very knowledgeable about my vehicle and even went to Pep Boys next store to make sure my Audi had the correct oil filter. I would definitely take my vehicle there again to see Mr. Castelow. Thank you Meineke. Sincerely, Gwendolyn Kent.
Very professional. Besides explaining the problem, they shied me the problem.

Since the Honda dealership is right up the road from me, we typically take our Hondas there. I had taken my vehicle to Meineke a few years ago for breakwork and had a great experience. Honda told me it would be $495 for the breakwork on my 2007 Honda Accord. I had to find another place, and I remembered my great experience with Meineke, so I made a call. Robert was a breath of fresh air. He was willing to help in every aspect! He made us feel like we were VIP customers and gave us special treatment helping in every way he could. He even went the extra mile to fix a piece that was coming off our windshield at no charge. This really went a long way since every penny counts. My husband even mentioned how Robert walked him out and shook his hand as he explained exactly what they did to his car. Please tell Robert how thankful we were for his graciousness. I will continue to bring my Honda and future vehicles here!  This service will certainly be mentioned to my friends and family!
Robert was very sweet.
The store manager was helpful and friendly.  He kept me appraised of the status of my vehicle (oil change and tire repair).  The cost of the service was very reasonable.
Tom and Eric are fantastic at what they do.  They are always friendly and professional. I typically go to their 82nd store  just south of King Road.
Gave me a better price than I originally expected.
Helped me understand what needed to be fixed and why. Also, very friendly.
Where I go, the guys at Meineke make me feel like I am taking my car to my brothers. They do a great job.  My car is a 2006 and it runs like new. Thanks to the guys at Meineke.
The staff at Meineke made my day.  They drove out to see me when I was stranded and made my visit well worth it.  They were kind, friendly and enjoyed having them work on my car.
I like the discount package of oil change that included tire rotation. I would also like to see discount on any military with ID card.
Ed and Ken are both very helpful and all employees are courteous.
Tom and Kenny have both been great to work with! Knowledgeable,friendly, accommodating, and always showing integrity in how they do business.

I needed my vehicle repaired. The first place I went to wanted to keep it over the weekend and suggested I rent a car. Meineke said I had a wait of 10 minutes. They checked the vehicle, told me the problem and ordered the part. I picked my vehicle up 2 hours later.

My wife and 2 little girls ended up at Meineke when their car overheated. I was in the mountains camping with my son. I was incredibly impressed to hear that your team bent over backwards to take such great care of them. I'm told they offered pizza to the girls, who hadn't eaten since breakfast, and that the manager on duty that day loaned my wife a vehicle so that she could get home to get the bank card needed to pay - as he and his team continued to work on the vehicle. We have lived in this area for almost 2 years and had yet to find a mechanic that treated us fairly and kindly enough to deserve our return business. Our unplanned visit to your car care centre changed that. We will be back!
Service was great and timely. Employees were very cooperative with the time and what needed to be done. They go out of their way to help customers.
Personally, I like that the staff is always willing to work with a person's budget.  :)
Staff was great. I just wish the parking lot was bigger.

I try to get my oil change done every three months. Every time I do one, the staff is friendly and quick to get it done for me. They refer me to other trusted mechanics and car shops if they aren't able to perform a task.
Explained everything well. They showed me the part of the car needing service to better explain the issue. Worked to get me the best price.

The rep was very helpful and told me the truth about the things I have been experiencing. They just wanted to help and not just tell me anything to spend more money. I will keep coming back here because I got what I asked for and was told the truth when I asked. Very honest place, and I appreciate that!

I get an oil change once a month due to the miles I drive. Buzz and Cindi are great to work with. They go above and beyond to make sure I am satisfied with their services. I got tires on my last visit and was not happy with them, so buzz replaced them. Would definitely recommend meineke on Melrose to anyone needing auto repairs on tires.
Bill kept his shop open an extra 1/2hr to finish my truck.
Customer service is always great  staff very helpful. Also, service always done when staff estimates it will be done!! I would definitely recommend this shop!!
I like the friendliness and helpfulness.
Bill was very responsive to my needs.  He is a professional in every sense of that word and his staff is friendly and professional as well!

The mechanic noticed that the oil drain plug was not fitting properly even after installing the new one we brought. The owner went out and tapped the threads and helped him choose a new drain plug to complete the job.  Since we were going to be traveling the next day, we were very grateful that he fixed the problem so that we would not breakdown on the highway.
The staff (particularly Mark) at the Hudson, NH Meineke are always friendly, knowledgable, professional and do a great job.
I travel out of my way to get my truck inspected and repaired by this location.

The staff at the Hudson, NH location is always very friendly and professional. I have been to this location several times and have always been seen on time and quickly. I always feel that what is recommended is important and needed. They do a great job, and I would recommend them to anyone. The waiting area is also comfortable with indoor seating and if it's a nice day, there's a picnic table outside. They always have kcups and snacks too, which is a nice touch. Overall, everything is clean and tidy.
Scheduled an apppointment, which worked out very smoothly.
Mike was very easy to work with. He didn't talk down to me and was very professional. I have been very pleased so far with the service & friendliness of the whole group at this location.
Tim in Highland Ranch is amazing!!
Manager was very good and knowledgeable. Even though they were almost closing, he got me in at the last minute and didn't make me come back. I really appreciated it.

Mike, the manager who I worked with, was awesome. He was honest and helpful. I had taken my SUV to another auto repair place for an estimate.  Mike worked with me to make sure what exactly the issue was. He also helped me to determine the best way to fix the issue without trying to sell me on anything else I didn't need.
Just very happy with the people and the service. I will always keep going back  to this Meineke. I have trust and faith in the people.

I am looking for a company that won't rip me off. So far, I have found it with  the meineke at the 5216 block of  broad street in Richmond, Va. Your service manager, Jamie, is very professional. I think I have found  the right company.

Jamie and his crew at the West Broad Street location in Richmond, VA are always the best!  They get you in and out. They also give you every recommendation possible, so they don't try to make you spend all your money. They will look at all other options just to try and save their customer's money.  Jamie makes it all about the customer! I will continue to go here for all car repairs that they can accommodate.  Thanks Jamie! -Mustang Sally
Great customer service.

I arrived with an emergency situation. Was greeted professionally and kindly by the young man at the desk. Very considerate to call me with an honest estimate so the work could be completed. Thank you so much to all the mechanics doing a great job.

I went in to have a tire put on my 2000 Pontiac Grand Am and an alignment done. The mechanic came out to the reception area and asked me to come with him.  He showed me how badly my car was rusted underneath. He explained to me that my tie rod end and sway bar was broken, so he was unable to do the alignment for me. He also made me aware that my car was unsafe to drive at that point. Once he removed what needed to be removed to fix the tie rod end and sway bar, then the car would be more difficult to repair. He also wasn't sure he would be able to put it back. I was so appreciative of this gentleman. I feel that if I had gone somewhere else, they would have tried to do the alignment and not told me about the other issue with my car.  I have only used Meineke for my car care needs. I used Pep Boys once. They were nice, but I will stick with Meineke.  After what I saw with my car, I do not drive it anymore.  Thank you Meineke for taking my safety seriously.

Kris is a fantastic manager. He really helped me with all the questions I had about my car and why it was acting up. He explained in detail the process that it would take to fix my car, which helped calm my nerves because it was initially about a check engine light. Overall, very knowledgeable and helpful! Kenny, the man who fixed my car, was very helpful when I came back with a question about a sound in my car. He went the extra mile to help and I have never met someone who cared more about truly helping the customer. My experience at Meineke was fantastic, and I will be back for all my future car needs!
Staff members are always so pleasant and helpful. The manager was great.  He took the time to answer all my questions.
Everything was repaired quickly and successfully.
Mike always helps me and he is awesome! He remembers me when I call or come in for assistance. He's just and overall helpful person. He's the reason why I keep coming back.

Carlos at this Meineke location was awesome. I am a young woman, so we sadly get taken advantage of at places like this where workers think we have no car knowledge and sell us up or other products. Carlos was fanastic at explaining and showing me everything they did with my car. He took me out into the shop to bring me under my car to show what was wrong. When I got home and my car was still leaking, Carlos told me to take it back to have him fix it again (faulty product placed in my car). While this left me feeling weird that after I left my car it still leaked, all the other customers in the room recommeded him.

Fred and his team continue to be wonderful. They are transparent, communicative, and not at all patronizing. As long as I own a car, I will bring it to this particular Meineke because of the expertise, service, and quality work.

The technician, Fred, was great. He didn't give me the usual, "Here's how much it costs to fix your problem..Oh and here's $1000 worth of other things to fix  that I got when I went to Monroe Muffler." He was honest and transparent about everything that needed to be repaired and got it done as quickly as possible. Great work. Will return to this store for any/all other repairs I need in the future.
The rep was courteous, friendly, and spoke like he knew what he is doing.

The sales associate at the front desk was amazing. They took care of me like I have been going to this shop for 10 years. I felt welcomed and at home as soon as I walked in the door. I got an oil change and state inspection. From the time I walked into the door and left with my keys in my hand, I was there for a total of 30 minutes. Received a hand written note after my visit, which was a great touch. Also, did a great job in repairing my AC unit. Very happy with the service!

Zach, Bob, and Sam, and the other staff at Meineke continually provide top quality service for our three vehicles. They were even able to quickly identify and fix a problem with my horse trailer. We will continue to bring our vehicles to them as long as we are in driving distance!

My car was making a weird noise. It was diagnosed but there was no pressure to repair or replace anything because the noise was benign. There was no charge for this assessment and honest feedback was very appreciated. Thank you, Zack!

Zach, the service manager, called to let me know of the other problem. After my okay, he completed the additional repair. I appreciate that the technicians check everything mechanical about my vehicle, and the service manager keeps me apprised of maintenance issues. The service level at the Scarborough, ME location is off the charts. I was a new customer and from the moment I walked in the door, I was treated like an old friend.. or even family. I got a great deal on my service and felt the whole crew was very honest and informative. Thank you!

My wife and I were on a road trip from Vancouver Island BC, Canada through the USA to Ontario. After a few days of driving, we noticed a bit of a squeak from the front left side of the truck. The wheel was very hot to the touch. It was Sunday and no one was picking up a phone in town so I could have it looked at. My wife noticed Meineke had an online booking, so we booked an appointment for Monday at 8.30 am. We went there as it was only about a 7 minute drive from our hotel where we were staying (Rapid City SD). The lady at the front desk was super helpful. The mechanic was also super helpful. He took a look once it was on the hoist. He had me come back and take a look to show me the front left calipre was on its way to seizing up. He told me all the different options, which were full replacement or just enough to get by. I told him we were trading the truck in at the end of the road trip (which we did) and I wanted it to be trouble free and safe enough to get us home. That's exactly what they did. We put another 8,000 kms in in 10 days. No problems. If Rapid City wasn't 5,000 Kms away and in a different country I would definitely go back haha. Really enjoyed it. In and out. Replaced and working in less than two hours. Very satisfied!

Great staff who answered all of my questions about their future recommendations and didn't push the services on me. Took the time to do a few other small adjustments since they already had the car lifted.
Trust and communication of car care experience.

I originally went to Firestone and they said I needed to get the belts replaced, but they were booked and referred me to a Freddie at Meineke. After that, I went to Meineke and they took me right in. They also recommended a fuel cleanse, which I wasn't sure if that was needed but was assured it would get the carbon build up off the plugs and better gas mileage (o.k. Thank you meineke for allowing me to get my car fixed so quickly and hassle free!  I believe the price was competetive because I did compare with other vendors...Thank you.

The customer service was great. I actually came in around 11 and they were swamped but were happy to set an appointment for 5 p.m.  I love the setup of the waiting area (I needed to charge my phone and you made it very easy to do that and handle some business on my wait). I was about to leave for a trip in the mountains, and I was worried about a vibration in the car. The team inspected the rotors at no additional charge and explained to me that it wasn't a dangerous situation. I plan to go back in the next week or so for them to determine if the rotor can be smoothed out. Overall, it was a very positive experience. Having a peace of mind that my car was safe was invaluable on my trip. As a side note, my parents visited this location when they first moved to the area because they needed a mechanic. In that one visit they received great service. They also  learned of a good vet and a real estate agent to help them find a house. More than 30 years later, I am so happy to find similarly helpful people in that same location. While this little corner between Sherwood and North Little Rock is growing tremendously, it still has that hometown feel.
Service was great and the staff was very nice!
